-- Germany's Henkel buys French laundry products group
-- By Victoria Bryan
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 12:58AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, June 5 (Reuters) - German consumer goods group Henkel & Co <HNKG_p.DE> has agreed to buy French laundry product group Spotless in a deal worth around 940 million euros ($1.28 billion), it said on Thursday.

The company was sold by private equity firm BC Partners, Henkel said on a statement.